text.__SUMMARY__: Parametaria dupontii, the Dupont's dove shell or false cone, is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae, the dove snails.
text.Description: Shells of Parametaria dupontii can reach a length of about 13–28 millimetres (0.51–1.10 in).
text.Distribution:
This species can be found in Gulf of California and in Pacific Mexico.
